question: Question: Keith Holyoake is the only person to have held the positions of Governor General and Prime Minister of this country. For 10 points each: [10] Name this country that has a February 6 public holiday to commemorate the signing of its founding document, the Treaty of Waitangi, between Captain William Hobson and hundreds of Maori chiefs.
